`autoUpdater.checkForUpdates()` is an asynchronous function that returns a promise. You can&#39;t catch these errors using a `try catch`.

This is how you catch errors:
```
autoUpdater.checkForUpdates().catch(err =&gt; {
    console.error(`Something went wrong`, err);
});
```

