A first approach is to use a variable as a mutex.

It will be set true at the beginning of the timer_Tick and then false at the end.

And before all, we wait that it is false.

    private volatile object _locker = new object();
    private volatile bool mutex = false;

    private void tmrfirst_Tick(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
      while ( mutex ) { }
      lock ( _locker )
        mutex = true;
      try
      {
        btnchecksignal.PerformClick();
        if ( textBox8.Text.Contains(&quot;+1&quot;) )
        {
          button14.PerformClick();
          button42.PerformClick();
          btnautostart.PerformClick();
        }
      }
      finally
      {
        lock ( _locker )
          mutex = false;
      }
    }

It is simple but you can add some cancellation conditions in the while loop.

But you may encounter sync problems with methods and UI.

It depends of what you want to do.

